@startuml mesmerize-multitenancy-silo
title Mesmerize Multitenancy — Mode A: Silo (Isolated DB)\nTenant = Organization | Clinic = sub-scope | S3 per-org isolation

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundCorner 8
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica

rectangle "Domain services\n(NestJS microservices)" as SVC #B3D4FC
queue "SQS\n(tenantId in message)" as SQS #B3D4FC
rectangle "Data access layer\nresolves connection by organizationId" as DATA #B3D4FC

database "Org config\ntenancyMode = silo" as CFG #E8E8E8

frame "Silo 1 — Organization A (tenantId=A)" as S1 {
  database "Aurora/Postgres\nDB for tenant A\n(only org A data)" as DBA #B3D4FC
  storage "S3\ns3://media/{A}/{clinicId}/...\nor dedicated bucket per org" as S3A #B3D4FC
}

frame "Silo 2 — Organization B (tenantId=B)" as S2 {
  database "Aurora/Postgres\nDB for tenant B\n(only org B data)" as DBB #B3D4FC
  storage "S3\ns3://media/{B}/{clinicId}/...\nor dedicated bucket per org" as S3B #B3D4FC
}

SVC --> SQS : publish/consume
SQS --> DATA
SVC --> DATA : REST/sync access
DATA --> CFG : read tenancyMode + connection
DATA --> DBA : route when tenantId=A
DATA --> DBB : route when tenantId=B
DATA --> S3A : objects for org A
DATA --> S3B : objects for org B

note bottom of DATA
  Physical DB isolation per Organization.
  Clinic/site is a folder + column inside the org DB,
  not a separate database.
  No cross-tenant connections.
end note

@enduml
